author: Inside Edition
description: The legends of Good Morning America are celebrating the show's golden anniversary. The very first anchor was David Hartman. He is now 90 years old. His co-anchor, Broadway star Nancy Dussault, is now 89. Joan Lunden was named co-anchor in 1980. Charlie Gibson joined the show in 1987, and Diane Sawyer stepped in as co-anchor in 1999. Three years later, she welcomed Robin Roberts. Now, George Stephanopoulos and Michael Strahan are part of the legacy.
title: 'Good Morning America' Celebrates 50th Anniversary

author: Inside Edition
description: A couple says that a girl was in danger of being swept out of a roller coaster, and they say they hung on to her for dear life. Chris Evins says he and his wife held onto the girl. He says the seats have two restraints, a lap bar, and a safety belt for each person. The ordeal lasted around 2 minutes until the ride came to an end. The park says it found no issues with the ride but out of an abundance of caution it replaced the lap belts and it has operated safely since the incident.
title: Adults Hold On To Girl In Danger Of Being Swept Out Of Roller Coaster

author: Inside Edition
description: Inside Edition headed over to Yummy Tummy's Kitchen in Brooklyn, New York where owner Melissa Johnson says there is so much you can do with mounds of leftover candy. Johnson says the candy can be used to make Thanksgiving dessert, just put them in the refrigerator to keep it fresh. She gave tips on how to make cookies and brownies with leftover candy. She says you can also elevate popcorn by covering it in chocolate.
title: Tips On What To Do With Leftover Halloween Candy

author: Inside Edition
description: Chaos as thousands of passengers wait for hours to go through security checks and flights are being delayed across America by a shortage of air traffic controllers turning up for work. What looks like being the longest government shutdown in history means that TSA agents and air traffic controllers are not getting paid. Up to 80% are taking other jobs to make ends meet. If the shutdown is not resolved soon, those delays will spill over into the Thanksgiving exodus, potentially ruining the holiday for millions.
title: Chaos At Airports As Government Shutdown Continues

author: Inside Edition
description: Cops in Plano, Texas, say a customer at a Spirit Halloween store brought their pet monkey with them to go shopping. The little guy seemingly decided to go looking for a costume on his own, got away from his owner, and ended up swinging from the rafters. Police showed up to the scene and were left scratching their heads. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Pet Monkey Gets Loose In Spirit Halloween In Texas

author: Inside Edition
description: Serial killer Joel Rifkin murdered at least 17 women, many of whom sex workers, between 1989 and 1993. But even as the victims' remains turned up, police never made the connection that it was the work of a single serial killer.
title: How Serial Killer Joel Rifkin Evaded Authorities For Years #shorts
